TEXT: amyloid convergence index for AV-45 subjects
NOTES: (1). Included baseline florbetapir PET with pre-processing QC passed for ADNI-DOD.   (2) this index (ACI) was generalized from the hypometabolic convergence index (HCI) for FDG-PET. ACI attempts to characterize the extent to which the amyloid deposition spatial pattern and magnitude in one individual subject match that in AD patients as a group. (3) SPM5  was used for image processing  by ADNI Analysis Team at BAI please contact Kewei Chen, Ph.D. (kewei.chen@bannerhealth.com) and Eric M. Reiman, M.D. (4) data subject to change due to addtion/change of subjects, time points and/or analysis type (5), the field name consists of two parts: part 1  is ACI, and part 2 is the reference region used in computing  the SUVR in generating ACI.
